# Success Criteria

The framework succeeds when:

* AI understands systems before modifying them.
* Documentation remains synchronized with implementation.
* Architectural decisions are traceable.
* Technical debt is continuously reduced.
* Engineering quality improves over time.
* Every iteration leaves the software in a healthier state.
* Knowledge persists across development cycles.
* Human engineers retain full visibility and control.

---

# Guiding Principle

> **Software is more than source code.**

Architecture, documentation, engineering knowledge, design decisions and continuous evolution are equally important components of a successful software system.

The OpenCode AI Engineering Kit exists to ensure that Artificial Intelligence contributes to every one of these dimensions with the discipline, transparency and repeatability expected from world-class engineering teams.
